Arsenal’s head coach, Mikel Arteta, has said he is ready to make one or two signings in January, to boost the squad. Arteta, who signed a three-and-a-half year deal to replace Unai Emery, has been assure by the board that there are funds available in the winter window. Emery signed the likes of Nicolas Pepe, David Luiz and Kieran Tierney last summer, but those arrivals were offset by the departures of Aaron Ramsey, Henrikh Mkhitaryan and Alex Iwobi. Speaking to Sky Sports, Arteta admitted he’s hopeful of up to two signings next month. “We need players back from injuries, first of all, to be more solid, more compact. “And then we might need to do one or two things if the right players become available, to help us. “But at the moment I am more concerned with getting the maximum out of the players available to us.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.